Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The results indicate suboptimal glycemic control (elevated HbA1c and fasting glucose), and dyslipidemia (high total cholesterol, LDL, and triglycerides). Renal function, electrolytes, and microalbumin/creatinine ratio are within normal limits. Recommend clinical follow-up for diabetes and lipid management to reduce cardiovascular risk.
